Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a red-brown pottery vessel, the fabric is grey in section, the interior is partially covered with a dark-brown resinous deposit, the exterior is covered with a red-orange slip and remains of three lines of black-painted demotic text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393772) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393772)
